{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9c9d8eaf-fd04-44f9-b020-907556dfe286","content":"Your project already has the HotReload package. To use it, run:\n\n```\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in **watch mode**. It will:\n\n1. Run your tests initially\n2. **Watch for file changes** — when you save edits to your test or source files, it automatically **re-runs the affected tests** without a full rebuild\n\nThis gives you a fast inner loop: fix a test → save → see results instantly.\n\n> **Tip:** Combine with `--filter` to focus on specific failing tests, e.g.:\n> ```\n> dotnet test --hotreload --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~EmailValidator\"\n> ```\n\nWould you like me to run it now so we can start iterating on the failures?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a1661b94-4dc4-42d5-a27a-47a91cd3ee94","outputTokens":181},"id":"8e4bb980-f41b-427b-a9d7-10d69cb07eb3","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:26.632Z","parentId":"8087af20-2fda-4f7c-ab3d-6501c6a0ab16"}
